# i18n-agent localization workflow

This project (or the user) uses i18n-agent: locale targets are translated through
the user's subscription via `npx i18n-agent …`. Rules:

- You author ONLY the source locale (`locales/<source>/…`). Move user-facing
  strings into keys there; never hardcode UI text.
- Never write translations into target locale files by hand — a hand-written
  value becomes human-owned and stops receiving machine updates. Targets are
  produced by `npx i18n-agent translate`.
- New project: `npx i18n-agent init` → `npx i18n-agent add-locale <lang> --translate`.
- After source-locale changes: `npx i18n-agent translate`. Before commit:
  `npx i18n-agent check` (CI gate, exit 1 on drift).
- Keep placeholders byte-identical in source edits: `{var}`, `{{var}}`,
  printf, `$t(...)`, HTML tags, ICU plural/select.
- "Awaiting review" keys (`npx i18n-agent translate --review`) are the USER's
  decision: hand-edit (resolves review), `--accept-stale`, or
  `--retranslate-stale`. Do not decide for them.
- Ambiguous strings get a hint in `i18n-agent.context.yaml`. `i18n-agent.lock` is
  committed and never edited by hand.
